# Feature Development Workflow

## Feature File Structure

Each feature is documented in `~/features` with four files:

### 1. `[feature-name].draft.md`
- Initial feature specification
- Requirements and acceptance criteria
- Design decisions and technical approach
- Created once at feature start
- NO technical information

### 2. `[feature-name].tech.md`
- Technical analysis of available components/composables
- Reusable code identification
- Third-party libraries or tools to use
- Technical constraints and dependencies
- folder structure draft

### 2.5. `[feature-name].research.md` (Optional)
- Web search
- 50 lines MAX
- Best practices for the feature domain
- CSS repositories and component libraries to reference
- Performance optimization techniques

### 3. `[feature-name].progress.md`
- Chronological log of development activities
- Files created/modified with explanations
- Bug fixes and why they were needed
- Implementation decisions and rationale
- Updated continuously during development

### 4. `[feature-name].tasks.md`
- Checklist of actionable tasks
- Mark completed tasks with `[x]`
- Add new tasks as they emerge
- Updated every work session

## Workflow

1. **Start feature**: Create `.draft.md` with requirements (AFTER: STOP and wait for input)
2. **Start feature**: Create `.tech.md` with requirements (AFTER: STOP and wait for input)
3. **Optional**: Create `.research.md` for complex features requiring best practices research
4. **During development**: Update `.progress.md` with changes and `.tasks.md` with task status
5. **Every session**: Review and update both progress and tasks files
6. **Feature complete**: All tasks marked `[x]`, progress documents final state

## Example Structure

```
.cursor/features/
  dark-mode.draft.md
  dark-mode.tech.md
  dark-mode.research.md (optional)
  dark-mode.progress.md
  dark-mode.tasks.md
  smooth-scroll.draft.md
  smooth-scroll.tech.md
  smooth-scroll.research.md (optional)
  smooth-scroll.progress.md
  smooth-scroll.tasks.md
```

## File Templates

### Draft Template
```markdown
# [Feature Name]

## Purpose
[Why this feature exists]

## Requirements
- Requirement 1
- Requirement 2

## Technical Approach
[How it will be implemented]

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Criterion 1
- [ ] Criterion 2
```

### Tech Template
```markdown
# [Feature Name] - Technical Analysis

## Available Components/Composables
- Component/hook name - location - purpose

## Reusable Code
- File path - what can be reused - why

## Third-Party Libraries
- Library name - purpose - why needed

## Technical Constraints
- Constraint description

## Proposed Folder Structure
path/to/feature/
├── Component1.tsx
├── Component2.tsx
└── styles.module.css
```

### Research Template (Optional)
```markdown
# [Feature Name] - Research & Best Practices

## Best Practices
- Performance optimization techniques
- Implementation patterns
- Common pitfalls to avoid

## Recommended Packages
- Package name - purpose - size/benefits

## CSS Repositories
- Resource name - URL - what to reference

## Accessibility Considerations
- Motion preferences
- Screen reader support
- Keyboard navigation

## Performance Targets
- Metrics to track
- Optimization checklist

## Resources & Learning
- Documentation links
- Inspiration sites
- Related articles
```

### Progress Template
```markdown
# [Feature Name] - Progress Log

## [Date] - Initial Implementation
- Created `src/components/Feature.tsx` - main component
- Modified `src/layout/index.tsx` - integrated feature
- Reason: [explain why]

## [Date] - Bug Fix
- Fixed: [describe bug]
- Changed: `src/components/Feature.tsx` line 42
- Root cause: [explain]
```

### Tasks Template
```markdown
# [Feature Name] - Tasks

- [ ] Task 1
- [ ] Task 2
- [x] Completed task
- [ ] New task discovered during development
```

## Naming Convention

- Simple, concise names: "scene2" not "scene2-redesign" or "scene2-split-screen"
- Avoid suffixes unless needed for disambiguation
- Use tree-style pipes (├── └──) for folder structures, not indentation

